<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870421-0066 </DOCNO><HL> GM Unit Gets$240.3 MillionIn Missile Work</HL><DD> 04/21/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> GM RTN TXN UTX GQ TDY BC MDAEROSPACE (ARO)DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Hughes Aircraft Co., a unit of General Motors Corp., won contracts totaling $240.3 million for Maverick missiles for the Air Force and missile testing for the Navy.    The Air Force also awarded Raytheon Co. a $147.7 million contract for Maverick missiles.    Texas Instruments Inc. got a $27.1 million Air Force contract for laser-guided bomb equipment.    Sikorsky Aircraft, a unit of United Technologies Corp., won Navy contracts totaling $21.4 million for SH-60F helicopter production and CH-53E helicopter improvements.    Grumman Aerospace Corp., a unit of Grumman Corp., received Navy contracts totaling $15.1 million for E-2C aircraft support and F-14 aircraft improvements.    The Army awarded Teledyne Inc. and Brunswick Corp. contracts of $13.7 million and $12.4 million, respectively, for camouflage screen systems.    Units of McDonnell Douglas Corp. received contracts totaling $11 million for aircraft improvements for the Air Force and Harpoon missile services for the Navy. </TEXT></DOC>